On US 97 Blewett Pass milepost 159-160 (near Swauk Creek Campground) Tuesday through Thursday from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. there is the potential for flagger controlled traffic with delays when the contractor is staging equipment. Traffic has been shifted to a bypass lane with a reduced speed limit and 12 ft. width restriction. The speed reduction and width restrict are in place 24/7. US 97 Boundary Bridge #9323 County: Kittitas Highway: US 97 Region: North Central Location: MP 159-160 (Swauk Campground) Description: In this $4.5M project WHH Nisqually Construction Services will construct a concrete bridge to replace an old culvert that created a fish passage barrier. Work will include a detour widening to shift traffic while the bridge is constructed half at a time. Two-way traffic will be maintained outside working hours throughout the life of the project except some instances of work that may require overnight flagging. No full closures of US 97 are planned for this project. Work schedule: Tuesda
